@startuml
title Szenario 4: Erweiterung eines Segment-Paars zur Chain

' Breite erzwingen
skinparam ParticipantPadding 60
skinparam BoxPadding 10
hide footbox

participant "Input" as IN
participant "ChainMatcher" as CM
participant "Extension" as EXT
participant "Scoring" as SC
participant "Endpoints" as EP
participant "ChainMatch" as OUT

IN -> CM: Initial match\nP0 Seg2 ↔ P1 Seg0 (92/85/100)

CM -> CM: 1. Initialize chain

CM -> EXT: 2. Extend chain

loop try_extend [forward & backward]
    ' Schritt: Zusammenfassung von Get Next & Align & Score in einem Call
    EXT -> SC: Get next (±1) & Score (Length/Dir/RMSD)

    ' Die Entscheidung visualisieren wir kompakt
    alt scores ≥ threshold
        SC --> EXT: ✓ Quality good (Extend)
    else quality drops
        SC --> EXT: ✗ Stop
    end
end

EXT -> EP: Chain complete (P0:[1,2,3] ↔ P1:[3,0,1])

' HIER SPAREN WIR PLATZ:
' Der Alt-Block für die Dot-Zuweisung wird zur Notiz
note right of EP
  **Endpoint Logic:**
  If first segment touches frame:
    blue=first, red=last
  Else:
    blue=last, red=first
end note

EP -> OUT: Create ChainMatch\n(ids, segments, scores, endpoints)

OUT --> CM: ChainMatch ✓ (Len:3, Score:89.7)

@enduml